# RiBuzz — high-risk paths

- **Next.js 16**: Do not assume pre-16 APIs. Check `node_modules/next/dist/docs/` when unsure.
- **`env` ([`src/lib/env.ts`](src/lib/env.ts))**: Server-only. Never import into `"use client"` files or shared modules used by the browser.
- **`publicEnv` ([`src/lib/public-env.ts`](src/lib/public-env.ts))**: Only `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for client bundles.
- **Service role**: [`src/lib/supabase/admin.ts`](src/lib/supabase/admin.ts) only on the server. Repositories used by [`createBackendServices`](src/services/bootstrap.ts) use the admin client by design; do not duplicate raw admin queries in route files without going through services.
- **Admin routes**: Start with [`requireAdminAccess`](src/services/admin-access-service.ts) — Bearer / `x-admin-api-key` for internal key, or Supabase session + `admin_profiles`.
- **Public API handlers**: Rate limit → validate body/query with Zod in [`src/lib/schemas/`](src/lib/schemas/) → [`apiOk` / `apiError` / `handleRouteError`](src/lib/api/response.ts). Preserve Turnstile and honeypot behavior where already implemented.
- **Schema changes**: Update [`supabase/migrations/`](supabase/migrations/) and [`src/types/database.ts`](src/types/database.ts) together.
- **API documentation**: Keep [`docs/API.md`](docs/API.md) in sync with any change to `src/app/api/**` (that file is the dedicated HTTP API reference).

Full context: root [`AGENTS.md`](AGENTS.md); HTTP API reference: [`docs/API.md`](docs/API.md).
